The paper focuses on using machine learning approaches based on natural language processing and social network analysis to detect real-life influence through Twitter. This involves analyzing the content of tweets and the relationships between users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as natural language processing is mentioned. cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing) is also relevant as the paper deals with social media and influence. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses ranking Twitter users based on their predicted influence level. Finally, cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible sub-category as the paper may touch on issues related to privacy and security on social media platforms.
